The paper proposes a new architecture for convolutional neural networks (CNNs) that improves performance and reduces the number of parameters. This is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The use of skip connections and channelwise concatenations is a common technique in deep learning (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The evaluation of the proposed architecture on object recognition and semantic segmentation datasets suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and image processing (cs.CL).
